VAT Naftokhimik Prykarpattya, a
Ukrainian oil refinery, said it had a net loss of about 52
million hryvnia ($6.4 million), in the first six months after a
net income of 47 million-hryvnia a year earlier, the company
said in a regulatory  statement  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
